		<title>Plan Your Next Vacation with Plan My Next Trip</title>
		<link>http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/09/30/plan-your-next-vacation-with-plan-my-next-trip/</link>
		<comments>http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/09/30/plan-your-next-vacation-with-plan-my-next-trip/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Sep 2011 16:54:19 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Kelly Clay</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Social]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.lockergnome.com/social/?p=4407</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I&#8217;m huge proponent of mental vacations, jetsetting off to another city for a weekend to clear my mind, seeing some friends, and checking out a different part of the country. Sometimes I spend part of this time alone, resigned to recommendations from friends and Yelp to find somewhere to eat lunch or grab a cup [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I&#8217;m huge proponent of mental vacations, jetsetting off to another city for a weekend to clear my mind, seeing some friends, and checking out a different part of the country. Sometimes I spend part of this time alone, resigned to recommendations from friends and Yelp to find somewhere to eat lunch or grab a cup of coffee in the afternoon. If you use Foursquare, you now have an even better way to plan your next mini-vacation with <a href="http://www.my-next-trip.com/">Plan My Next Trip</a>.</p>
<p>Plan My Next Trip is the winner of Foursquare&#8217;s recent second hackathon, beating 100 other Foursquare apps to win the event. Plan My Next Trip is a Web app that taps into the Foursquare API and generates a two-day itinerary of things to do, places to see, and restaurants to visit. Even people who are not Foursquare users can use Plan My Text Trip to build a schedule when visiting a different city, as it returns ideas based on the popularity of places on Foursquare.</p>
<p><img class="alignright size-large wp-image-4408" src="http://www.lockergnome.com/social/files/2011/09/Plan-your-next-trip-1-300x134.jpg" alt="Plan My Next Trip" width="300" height="134" />If you happen to have several friends in a different city who use Foursquare, Plan My Next Trip will work best. The app will create an itinerary using the places your friends have checked in to as well as those that are most popular. The more friends who have checked in to places in a city and also left reviews will weigh more heavily than the overall popularity of a location.</p>
<p>Users who are visiting a new survey will only want to use this app as a guide, however, as I was recommended questionable parks to visit in the afternoon and grocery stores to &#8220;pick something up.&#8221; Plan My Next Trip was otherwise generally helpful in generating an itinerary for my upcoming trip to San Francisco. Just make sure that if you do, in fact, use Fourssquare, you check the box when entering the city to search for, or else you will not receive personalized results based on your Foursquare friends.</p>
<p>Check out <a href="http://www.my-next-trip.com/">Plan My Next Trip</a> and let us know what you think of the app in the comments.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/09/30/plan-your-next-vacation-with-plan-my-next-trip/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
