		<title>Google Bookmarks is a Free Alternative to Delicious</title>
		<link>http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/09/30/google-bookmarks-is-a-free-alternative-to-delicious/</link>
		<comments>http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/09/30/google-bookmarks-is-a-free-alternative-to-delicious/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Sep 2011 16:47:16 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Kelly Clay</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Social]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.lockergnome.com/social/?p=4416</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Earlier this year, Yahoo! made the shocking decision to shut down Delicious, the popular bookmarking site that also helped users discover other content as well. Delicious was then bought by AVOS, which has now completely revamped Delicious and changed the entire concept of the service. Delicious has relaunched with a new design in beta, attempting [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Earlier this year, Yahoo! made the shocking decision to shut down Delicious, the popular bookmarking site that also helped users discover other content as well. Delicious was then bought by AVOS, which has now completely revamped Delicious and changed the entire concept of the service. Delicious has relaunched with a new design in beta, attempting to recreate the wheel with some new features that are either very similar to the previous function of Delicious or missing the point entirely &#8212; but both with enough bugs to make the service generally unusable for the time being.</p>
<p>For (pissed off) former-Delicious users who are now looking for a free alternative to Delicious, consider <a href="https://www.google.com/bookmarks/l">Google Bookmarks</a>. This service functions very similarly to the old Delicious, and features public lists created by other users. These lists are searchable, so if you are looking for bookmarks related to vegan food, for instance, you can simply type in &#8220;vegan&#8221; and dozens of lists created by other Google users will be returned with bookmarks to topics related to vegan living, dieting, cooking, and related issues. Google Bookmarks users can also easily import their Delicious bookmarks to assist with a complete transition away from the new Delicious.</p>
<p>Google Bookmarks is only available to Google users, but is easily accessible when logged in to other Google services. Google Bookmarks also features a bookmarklet for Chrome users, so Google Bookmarks users can easily bookmark a link without having to copy and paste URLs between browser windows or tabs.</p>
<p>Google Bookmarks is one of the most easy to use, intuitive alternatives to Delicious. For those looking for more functionality, such as tags, <a href="http://pinboard.in/">Pinboard</a> is another great alternative, though it is not free. Signing up for a Pinboard account will cost $9.45, but does offer more features that former Delicious users expect in a bookmarking site.</p>
<p>Are you a former user of Delicious? If you now use another bookmarking service, let us know your favorite in the comments below.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/09/30/google-bookmarks-is-a-free-alternative-to-delicious/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
