		<link>http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/09/30/track-your-twitter-growth-with-twitter-counter/</link>
		<comments>http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/09/30/track-your-twitter-growth-with-twitter-counter/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Sep 2011 16:38:48 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Kelly Clay</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Social]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.lockergnome.com/social/?p=4402</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[If you&#8217;re running a social media campaign for a brand or business, you know how critical it is to be able to prove that your presence on social platforms like Facebook and Twitter is increasing. There are several apps that can display data like growth of followers, but they are often bundled with social media [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>If you&#8217;re running a social media campaign for a brand or business, you know how critical it is to be able to prove that your presence on social platforms like Facebook and Twitter is increasing. There are several apps that can display data like growth of followers, but they are often bundled with social media management tools like HootSuite or Tap11, and these reports are not often free. If you&#8217;re looking for a report of you or your brand&#8217;s growth on Twitter as defined by number of followers, those you follow, and total tweets, Twitter Counter may just be the tool you are looking for.</p>
<p>Twitter Counter is a freemium tool that quickly and easily shows the growth of your Twitter account over the past six months. You can see the trend of new followers, those you are following, and your tweets. For an additional $15 a month, users can upgrade an account to generate more reports about followers and those who are followed through the past year, as well as see reports about the trends of your @mentions and retweets. With a premium account, users can also export stats to Excel or download PDF reports.</p>
<p><img class="alignright size-large wp-image-4403" src="http://www.lockergnome.com/social/files/2011/09/Kelly-Clay-Twitter-Stats-Twitter-Counter-300x159.jpg" alt="Twitter Counter" width="300" height="159" />For those of you not looking for your Twitter account growth patterns beyond the past six month, you may want to augment these reports with those generated by <a href="https://metricly.com/">Metricly</a>, which show the trend of your tweets, @mentions, and retweets, but don&#8217;t generate a report of your followers. Using only the features of both Metricly and Twitter Counter, users can get a comprehensive picture of growth (and success) of you or your brand&#8217;s Twitter account &#8212; and it is also free. Additionally, you can opt in to receiving emails about your Twitter data, making it even easier to stay on top of your Twitter account&#8217;s exact growth.</p>
<p>If you manage a social media account using Twitter, how do you track the growth and success of your campaign? Let us know your favorite tools in the comments below.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/09/30/track-your-twitter-growth-with-twitter-counter/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
