		<title>How to Unfollow People on Twitter</title>
		<link>http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/09/29/how-to-unfollow-people-on-twitter/</link>
		<comments>http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/09/29/how-to-unfollow-people-on-twitter/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Sep 2011 17:56:48 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Kelly Clay</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Social]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.lockergnome.com/social/?p=4376</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[There are dozens of reasons to unfollow someone on Twitter. Perhaps they only post inane updates about their shopping habits, or spam their followers with all the gossip fit for both celebrity and tech blogs. Perhaps you&#8217;re concerned about your Klout score, and need to reduce the ratio of those you follow and those following [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>There are dozens of reasons to unfollow someone on Twitter. Perhaps they only post inane updates about their shopping habits, or spam their followers with all the gossip fit for both celebrity and tech blogs. Perhaps you&#8217;re concerned about your Klout score, and need to reduce the ratio of those you follow and those following you. Or perhaps you don&#8217;t actually read the updates from the majority of those you follow, and don&#8217;t see a need to actually be following them.</p>
<p>For whatever reason you want to unfollow someone, you can always use Twitter.com to manually unfollow specific users. However, if you want to unfollow several types of people &#8212; such as by who is not following you or hasn&#8217;t posted recently &#8212; you can use tools like Refollow and JustUnfollow to help you clean out your Twitter house.</p>
<p><img src="http://www.lockergnome.com/social/files/2011/09/how-to-unfollow-twitter.gif" border="0" alt="How to Unfollow People on Twitter" hspace="3" vspace="3" width="200" align="right" /><strong><a href="http://www.justunfollow.com/">JustUnfollow</a></strong> is a simple Web app that uses Twitter&#8217;s API to determine who is not following you back. While this seems like a narcissistic reason to unfollow someone at first, keep in mind that Twitter is about relationships and discussions. If they&#8217;re not contributing to your discussions by reading your tweets, you clearly don&#8217;t have a relationship (at least on Twitter) with that user. While the lack of reciprocal follows can be useful to read tweets from media and thought leaders, there is no reason to follow anyone else who doesn&#8217;t follow you. To get rid of such people you follow, JustUnfollow is a great solution.</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re looking to unfollow more than just those who do not follow you &#8212; or unfollow other types of users, such as inactive ones &#8212; <strong><a href="http://refollow.com/">Refollow</a></strong> is a better option. With this tool, Twitter users can generate a list of Twitter users based on several options &#8212; such as when they last tweeted, if they have a picture or not, or if they have ever sent an @mention to you &#8212; to unfollow even users who follow you back but aren&#8217;t being engaging with you.</p>
<p>Twitter users, let us know if and why you unfollow other Twitter users and your favorite tools to help in the comments below.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/09/29/how-to-unfollow-people-on-twitter/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
